.TH PUTCTL1 9 "@PACKAGE_DATE@" "@PACKAGE@-@VERSION@" "@PACKAGE_TITLE@ DDI/DKI"
.\"
.\"
.SH NAME
.B putctl1
\- put a 1 byte control message on a \fISTREAMS\fR message queue
.\"
.\"
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
.B #include <sys/stream.h>
.HP
.BI "int putctl1(queue_t *" q ", int " type ", int " param );
.\"
.\"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.I q
the queue to which to put the control message.
.PD 0
.TP
.I type
the type of the control message.
.TP
.I param
a one-byte parameter to place in the message.
.PD
.\"
.\"
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
.BR putctl1 ()
creates a one-byte control message of type
.I type
with the one-byte data containing the data
.I param
and invokes the put procedure of the queue pointed to by
.I q
to place the message on the queue.
If
.I type
is a data message type
.RB ( M_DATA "(9), " M_PROTO "(9) or " M_PCPROTO (9))
and not a control message type,
.BR putctl1 ()
will fail.
Note that
.BR putctl1 ()
can succeed for message type
.BR M_DELAY (9),
which is normally a data message type according to
.BR datamsg (9).
.\"
.\"
.SH RETURN
.PP
Upon success,
.BR putctl1 ()
returns true (1).
Upon failure,
.BR putctl1 ()
returns false (0).
.\"
.\"
.SH ERRORS
.PP
.BR putctl1 ()
fails and returns false (0) if the specified
.I type
is not a control message type or if allocation of the necessary message block fails.
.\"
.\"
.SH CONTEXT
.PP
.BR putctl1 ()
can be called from any context, including user context, module procedures,
callouts, callbacks, soft interrupts and interrupt service routines;
however, see the considerations listed under
.BR put (9).
.\"
.\"
.SH MP-STREAMS
.PP
.BR putctl1 ()
is MP-safe; however, see the considerations listed under
.BR put (9).
.\"
.\"
.SH NOTICES
.PP
.BR putctl1 ()
can succeed with a
.I type
argument of
.BR M_DELAY (9).
.\"
.\"
.SH IMPLEMENTATION
.PP
Message blocks allocated by
.BR putctl1 ()
are allocated with priority
.BR BPRI_HI .
.\"
.\"
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.PP
.BR datamsg (9),
.BR freezestr (9),
.BR put (9),
.BR putctl (9),
.BR putnextctl (9),
.BR putnextctl1 (9).
.\"
.\"
.SH BUGS
.PP
.BR putctl1 ()
has no known bugs.
.\"
.\"
